description:
ACUMENTUS is a global boutique management consulting or advisory firm focused on empowering the world’s foremost public and private institutions to achieve optimal efficient growth by helping organizations refine their strategic vision, revolutionize operational efficiency, and foster the development of data-driven, agile solutions for unparalleled success. 
  
We specialize in: 
-accelerating comprehensive business transformation in areas spanning technology, business processes and real estate rationalization; 
-creating effective change management, social impact and cultural evolution;  
-optimizing human capital and leadership enhancement; 
-institutionalizing resiliency and crisis preparedness in local global organizations. 

Our approach leverages qualitative and quantitative measures that unlock the full spectrum of potential within portfolios and performance. Through collaborative efforts, we co-create inclusive initiatives and policies, delineate precise roadmaps to value realization, and shepherd clients through seamless end-to-end implementation. 
  
Under our stewardship, institutions embark upon transformations aimed at delivering streamlined services and products to clients and constituents, nurturing a diverse and empowered workforce, and forging deeper connections with external stakeholders. These endeavors fortify their global standing and competitive edge, enabling them to thrive in dynamic markets and communities.

Building Safer Communities LLC provides prevention, intervention, education and training services.

Services include: 
Education and Sports Basketball Team; 
Recovery Coaching;
Recovery Coach Training; 
Parenting Workshops; 
NYS Impaired Driving (drugs & alcohol) classes;
Domestic Violence classes; 
Anger Management classes;
Work Place Bullying workshops; 
Offender Workforce Development (OWD); 
Interactive Journaling;
Supportive Services for individuals, families and couples;
Adverse Childhood Experiences (ACE's) Training; 
Live Internet Radio Shows (community involvement).

Burrell Law, P.C. provides legal services for: 
*Business entity, special purpose vehicle (SPV) or other organization formation and structuring;
*Early-stage (seed) funding agreements and operational financing; *Contract drafting and negotiation (such as term sheets and agreements for convertible notes, preferred stock and other equity & debt issuances);
*Private placement offering memoranda (PPM);
*Reverse mergers, asset sales and other mergers and acquisitions;
*1993 Securities Act & 1934 Exchange Act legal advisory, including, disclosure counsel;
*Bond counsel;
*Virtual currency, cryptocurrency and other crypto-assets legal advisory;
*Renewable energy industry agreements (Power Purchase Agreements); and, 
*Domestic and international corporate tax advisory.

Dedicated to promoting African-centered holistic principles and providing a sacred support system, as a learning institute, where we advocate holistic alternatives; with a special focus on the health care needs of people of color.  We promote holistic lifestyle modalities that honor the whole person (mind, body, spirit) and encourage people to actively participate in their own health & wellness.

We are a support group for holistic health practitioners;
We offer continuing education to the holistic health community;
We are a holistic educational resource to the community at large;
We connect holistic health practitioners to the community in need of service;
We bring holistic health services to the community via various events and festivals;
We staff health & wellness for private, nonprofits,  community and governmental events

Pathway Partners LLC is a certified MBE and Service-Disabled Veteran-Owned (SDVOSB) management and technical services business. Our collective experience reflects expert knowledge in network infrastructure architecture & engineering, telecommunications, cybersecurity, data entry, data engineering and analytics, and network migration/transition/sustainment management services. Our service offerings include: 
a) Enterprise IT 
***Network Engineering, Design, Implementation, & O&M: Design, develop, test, and deploy network infrastructure and operate and manage IT services (LAN/WAN/WLAN); 
***Cybersecurity: Provide multidisciplinary experts across all domains to protect and secure data, assets, applications, infrastructure, and users; 
b) Data Analysis and Digitization 
***Document Review/Categorization: Understanding the customer’s underlying categorization schema, staffers screen, qualify, and correlate incoming data; 
***Accurate Data Entry: Staffers keenly enter pertinent data into appropriate system fields, while a backend data quality review process ensures accuracy; 
***Performance Analytics: Provide timely and accurate decision support using advanced techniques (e.g. Python, R, Tableau) that analyze and contextualize large sets of data; 
***Low-/No-code Data Solutions: Using existing MS 365 capabilities (e.g., Sharepoint, SQL), expert coders can create new data schemas, create digital forms, and produce custom reports that reduce administrative burden, increase accuracy, and inform decisions. ***Artificial Intelligence (AI)/Machine Learning (ML) Development and Support: Develop, enhance, and evolve models to solve and eliminate complex business and or technical challenges; 
c) Project Management 
***Project Implementation Management: Configure, deploy, and maintain WAN/LAN/ Datacenter network devices throughout the IT enterprise. 
***Program Migration/Transition Management: Manage seamless migrations of applications and networks to new environments; 
d) Staff Augmentation 
***IT Staff Augmentation: Provide additional IT staff to an organization to assist with software development, network management, cybersecurity, and other IT-related tasks. 
***Administrative Staff Augmentation: Provide additional administrative professionals to an organization to assist with clerical work, scheduling, customer service, and other administrative tasks. ***Customer Service Staff Augmentation: Provide additional customer service professionals to an organization to assist with answering customer inquiries, handling complaints, and other customer service-related tasks. 
e) Law Enforcement Strategy and Support 
***Intelligence Strategy: Improve how operational data can inform strategic plans and tactical decisions by identifying additional data resources 
***Investigation Support: Provide additional personnel, who analyze records, conduct interviews, summarize investigative efforts, and/or contribute to investigative findings 
***Compliance Auditing: Identify compliance gaps by reviewing internal records and procedures to ensure compliance with federal/state/local and internal codes. 
f) Survey Administration 
***CATI/CAPI Survey Data Collection: Perform interviews and enter data into systems 
***Survey Design and Question Drafting: Where appropriate, draft individual questions or design surveys related to affordable housing

From our inception, Teq has focused on creating positive outcomes and experiences for our educational partners. We are committed to providing full service solutions from the very beginning of the project through to its completion, setting us apart from other Professional Development providers. 

Teq’s Professional Development (PD) program is designed to improve technology integration through nurturing and supporting School Leader and Teacher capacity, pedagogy, and creativity. To this end, we work with educational professional from all ends of the spectrum (in-service teachers, pre-service teachers, students, and administrators). Our PD Department is committed to helping educators create collaborative and engaging learning environments designed specifically to enhance and optimize learning. We understand that School Leaders and Teachers operate in a complex and chaotic ecology where success depends on improvising knowledgeable answers to largely unanticipated problems (Mishra, 2000). As a result, we have created a model that allows us to provide comprehensive professional development services to schools and districts as a whole, while differentiating the PD offered for each educator, i.e., Teachers, Coaches, Students, and Administrators).  

Teq’s comprehensive Professional Development (PD) services are designed to facilitate an in-depth understanding of today’s educational technologies (interactive panels/whiteboards, instructional support software, computers, Chromebook, iPads, Mobile Devices, etc.), and to effectively integrate topics such as Computer Sciences, STEM, Coding/Programming, Robotics into teaching and learning. To accomplish these goals, Teq’s team of State Certified Educators (Curriculum Specialists and Professional Development Specialists) work directly with Teachers, Students, and Administrators providing PD, along with content specific examples designed to assist the infusion of these essential educational tools and instructional resources curriculum and instruction. Teq’s PD services focus on the following areas: 

•	Understanding and leveraging the benefits of technology for Teachers, Students, and Administrators; 
•	Enabling both Teachers and Students to use technology proficiently; 
•	Providing insight into the best practices that will optimize educational outcomes; 
•	Collaborating with School Leaders and Teachers as they utilize technology, suggesting ways to move beyond monitoring student progress and helping to create instructional rich environments that support and bolster the unique learning styles of students; and 
•	Working with School Leaders and Teachers to review and plan projects and lessons based on the Universal Design for Learning (UDL), TPACK, and SAMR models; thereby integrating the most current research-based design principles and solutions into teaching and learning. 

Teq employs well over 20 Curriculum and PD Specialists, all of whom are State Certified Educators; SMART Master Certified Trainers; Google Certified Educators; Microsoft Innovate Educators; and Apple Trainer. These full-time employees of Teq are also subject matter experts and have obtained teaching certifications that reflect almost every subject and grade level – Elementary, Middle, and High School; Math, Science (STEM), ELA, and Social Studies; and Special Education and English Language Learners (ELL/ESL/ENL). 

The diversity of our Professional Development Team is an integral part of our success and profoundly influences the way we support schools throughout NYC, NYS, NJ, and beyond. Each of our Curriculum and PD Specialists possess classroom teaching experience, subject matter expertise, sound pedagogical knowledge, strong technological skills, and exceptional interpersonal skills allowing them to seamlessly translate their knowledge using a combination of demonstrations, hands-on practice, workshops, and classroom coaching & mentoring.
